description: The Duveen Brothers was a firm of influential art dealers from the late nineteenth to the mid-twentieth century based in London, Paris, and New York. With Joseph Duveen (1869-1939) at the helm and the assistance of art experts, most notably Bernard Berenson (1865-1959), Duveen Brothers played a prominent role in the transfer of old master paintings, antique furnishings, and objets d'art from Europe to the United States. Albums and portfolios in Series I.C. contain reproductions of Greek relief sculpture and vases, Italian paintings, sculptures and fountains, and of Italian and French architecture.
